.TH smi-diskless-passwd "1" "October 2025" "SMI Toolset 0.100.0" "SMI Diskless Command"
.SH NAME
smi-diskless-passwd \- Set or change a user password in a diskless environment
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B smi-diskless-passwd
.I DISKLESS_NAME
.I USER_NAME
.SH DESCRIPTION
.PP
.B smi-diskless-passwd
allows setting or changing the password for a user within the specified \fIDISKLESS_NAME\fR environment.
The process involves:
.IP 1.
Temporarily disabling SELinux enforcement (\fBsetenforce 0\fR) on the host to allow the chroot operation.
.IP 2.
Performing a \fBchroot\fR(8) into the diskless root directory and executing \fBpasswd\fR(8).
.IP 3.
Re-enabling SELinux enforcement (\fBsetenforce 1\fR) after the command finishes.
.SH AUTHOR
.PP
Command written by Imre Tabur.
Documentation written by Imre Tabur.
